 - Good morning, church.

2
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:04,460
 It's good to see you.

3
00:00:04,460 --> 00:00:07,300
 I know there's a lot of you watching from different places,

4
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:08,420
 so I know you're there,

5
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:11,040
 and so thank you for joining us this morning.

6
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:14,480
 Church, I want to start by recapping our last two weeks

7
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:15,800
 from the Advent series.

8
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,560
 In week one, we talked about the call

9
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,940
 and that there's 400 years of silence,

10
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:23,020
 people's hearts got hardened,

11
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:26,640
 and no one expected Jesus to come, but he did.

12
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:30,040
 And Andrew focused on the call of repentance,

13
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:31,840
 which is a call to turn around,

14
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:34,460
 to reorientate yourself in a new direction,

15
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:36,440
 and it speaks more of action

16
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:38,940
 and more than just a confession.

17
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:42,600
 And John the Baptist shows us that Advent is a call

18
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:46,320
 to personal renewal as well as social reversal.

19
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,340
 Last week, which you probably remember,

20
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:50,880
 we talked about this beautiful place called the desert,

21
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:52,920
 and we focused on the wilderness

22
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:55,080
 and how that it plays a central role

23
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,720
 in the Old Testament biblical narrative,

24
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:00,840
 and this is where God most revealed himself to his people,

25
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:04,040
 and he did it through a process in the wilderness

26
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:07,000
 through intimacy, through teaching, and through healing.

27
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:11,340
 Also, we just dwelled on the fact that Advent is a time

28
00:01:11,340 --> 00:01:14,320
 for us to redefine our own wilderness,

29
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:19,020
 from a place of isolation to a place where we can meet God.

30
00:01:19,020 --> 00:01:21,320
 And we must remember that this is the coolest thing,

31
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:23,880
 that there is fruit in the desert,

32
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:28,160
 and that God will stop at nothing in our wilderness

33
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:33,160
 to shape and refine us so that we could be fully alive in him.

34
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:37,320
 And so before I start, I have a disclaimer to make.

35
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:41,440
 Although we are gonna be talking about baptisms,

36
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:44,880
 my intention, for those of you who are already baptized,

37
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:48,160
 whether in November or you got baptized earlier,

38
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:51,360
 I do not wanna cause any one of you to second doubt

39
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:53,120
 or second guess your baptism, right?

40
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,160
 The fact that you got baptism, that's good.

41
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:58,840
 Now, for those of you who have not gone baptized yet,

42
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:01,400
 every year we run a few courses throughout the year

43
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,720
 where you can learn more about baptism,

44
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:07,200
 and hopefully it'll help you make an informed decision

45
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,800
 on whether to get baptized or not.

46
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,840
 So there's more information on that.

47
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:14,100
 So in the last two months,

48
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:16,660
 I've been preparing to share with you today,

49
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:20,200
 and three things came to mind

50
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,000
 that I wanna bring to your attention,

51
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,920
 and these things hinder our faith and hinder our growth,

52
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:29,000
 and they are distractions, they are hurries,

53
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,880
 and they are desires.

54
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,280
 And so I just want you to reflect

55
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:35,720
 on whether these things impact your faith or not.

56
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:37,800
 So church, I wanna ask you,

57
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:41,680
 how often do you get distracted from what you need to do

58
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,440
 and are called to do?

59
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:46,080
 Think about Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane,

60
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:49,160
 and how many times did Jesus have to ask his disciples

61
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,120
 to stay focused and to just pray with him?

62
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,280
 Because often there is so much going on,

63
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:57,460
 not just externally, but internally in us,

64
00:02:57,460 --> 00:03:01,080
 that our hearts and our focus gets divided.

65
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,000
 Let me ask you another thing.

66
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:07,600
 How often are you hurrying from one thing to another,

67
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:12,200
 one place to another, from one conversation to another?

68
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,280
 Lately I'm realizing that hurry

69
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:17,880
 is one of the greatest enemies to our spirituality,

70
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:22,280
 because we simply cannot do what Jesus asks of us

71
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,960
 in a hurry.

72
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:26,540
 We cannot follow him to a quiet place in a hurry.

73
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,640
 We cannot build meaningful relationships in a hurry.

74
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:33,620
 We cannot listen to what God wants to say to us in a hurry.

75
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:36,640
 And lastly, I want you to think about this, church.

76
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:40,880
 How often do you experience a perpetual restlessness

77
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:43,580
 within your heart that you can't get rid of?

78
00:03:43,580 --> 00:03:46,940
 As humans, we have desires, and they drive and motivate us,

79
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:49,520
 and we get stuff done, which is great.

80
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,920
 But the tension arises when we realize

81
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,720
 that we're actually finite beings.

82
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,180
 That means we have limitations,

83
00:03:55,180 --> 00:04:00,180
 but yet our hearts desire infinitely so much stuff.

84
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:02,200
 And what happens then?

85
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,760
 We experience this thing called restlessness.

86
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:07,800
 We can't stay still, and no matter how much we see,

87
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,680
 no matter how much we do, buy, sell, eat, drink,

88
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:14,280
 experience, visit, travel, we always want more.

89
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,840
 We can't seem to satisfy that.

90
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,680
 And we do try to satisfy that.

91
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,200
 We try to manage that ourselves,

92
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:23,600
 but then we're led down this path of more anxiety,

93
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,440
 of depression, of burnout, of materialism,

94
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,260
 of sin, idolatry.

95
00:04:28,260 --> 00:04:32,780
 We form these unhealthy habits and attachments to things,

96
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:36,020
 all as a way of us trying to address our restlessness

97
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:39,400
 that actually only God can satisfy.

98
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,040
 And we continue to spiral

99
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,520
 unless we encounter some kind of intervention.

100
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:47,560
 And so the danger and consequence of being distracted,

101
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:50,640
 of hurrying, letting our desires consume us,

102
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:54,800
 is how easily we remove ourselves from God's presence

103
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,780
 and out of his speaking range.

104
00:04:56,780 --> 00:05:01,440
 Our manic lifestyles, whether you realize it or not,

105
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,960
 disconnects and actually threatens our connection

106
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,220
 with our living God.

107
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:08,400
 And of course, God knows we've done,

108
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,480
 we've tried everything we can to fix this and to help this,

109
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:15,720
 but perhaps our solution to these states

110
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,720
 that we find ourselves in isn't found in reduction

111
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:22,560
 or in elimination, but rather in a redirection

112
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,480
 to what God has for us.

113
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:27,840
 Church, in this period of Advent,

114
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:31,100
 God redirects our attention back to him,

115
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,680
 back to what he's saying,

116
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:35,920
 back to what is most important to him.

117
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,960
 He directs the church, that is us,

118
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,160
 to reflect on our readiness

119
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:43,400
 and to anticipate his son, his second coming,

120
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:46,240
 but more importantly and just as important,

121
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,480
 God redirects our attention to remind us

122
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,240
 that Jesus is already with us,

123
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:53,200
 he's already present in our life right now.

124
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:59,120
 And God reminds us that he has given us the spirit

125
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,320
 so that we don't have to walk each day alone

126
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,580
 or without any help.

127
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:08,720
 So church, this morning, I just want to let God address you.

128
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:12,160
 I want him to, I've been praying

129
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,380
 that he would show you something about himself

130
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,200
 or that he would just remind you of something

131
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,760
 that he wants you just to remember,

132
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,020
 just to continue to work in,

133
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:22,040
 something he wants to encourage you in,

134
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,300
 something he wants to comfort you in.

135
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,520
 And as Andrew said, God does not condemn.

136
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,960
 He reminds us because he loves us.

137
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:32,700
 And so today, as we talk about the baptism,

138
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:35,400
 we're not gonna go verse by verse as we're used to.

139
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,600
 I would like to share God's desire,

140
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:40,200
 his heart for the church that is us

141
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,400
 and what it means to be baptized.

142
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,700
 And so I pray that God would reveal this to you today.

143
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,680
 So church, I'm just gonna pray for us.

144
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,980
 So would you pray with me?

145
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:57,000
 Lord, I have done my humanly best to prepare for today.

146
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:01,420
 And only you, Lord, can say what you want to say

147
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:05,600
 to each of my family members listening, wherever they are.

148
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,500
 So Lord, I surrender this morning to you

149
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,280
 and I trust that you will speak

150
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,640
 because I will say a lot of things this morning,

151
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,320
 but I pray that you would just say that one thing

152
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,420
 to each person as they need it

153
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:18,920
 and that it would change them, it would form them,

154
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,320
 it would transform them.

155
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:22,680
 And you are with us.

156
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,520
 Lord, thank you, in your name we pray, amen.

157
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:29,280
 So with that, we are gonna jump into our passage today.

158
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:32,680
 We're in Mark chapter one, verse one to eight.

159
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,320
 Please read with me.

160
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,880
 The beginning of the good news about Jesus,

161
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,440
 the Messiah, the Son of God,

162
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,840
 as it is written in Isaiah the prophet.

163
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:43,000
 I will send my messenger ahead of you

164
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,800
 who will prepare your way,

165
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,140
 a voice of one calling the wilderness.

166
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:51,040
 Prepare the way for the Lord, make straight paths for him.

167
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,240
 And so John the Baptist appeared in the wilderness

168
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,980
 preaching a baptism of repentance

169
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:56,700
 for the forgiveness of sins.

170
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,360
 The whole Judean countryside

171
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:01,360
 and all the people of Jerusalem went out to him,

172
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,500
 confessing their sins.

173
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:05,240
 They were baptized by him in the river Jordan.

174
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,480
 John wore clothing made of camel's hair

175
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,220
 with a leather belt around his waist

176
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:12,000
 and he ate locusts and wild honey.

177
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,480
 And this was his message.

178
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:17,600
 After me comes one more powerful than I,

179
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,280
 the straps of whose sandals I am not worthy

180
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:22,240
 to stoop down and untie.

181
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,040
 I baptize you with water,

182
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:27,580
 but he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.

183
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:31,480
 This passage marks the beginning

184
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,800
 of how Jesus became the Messiah

185
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:35,160
 and how he was introduced.

186
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:38,560
 And it starts with the Old Testament prophecy from Isaiah

187
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:42,680
 and how John the Baptist was the fulfillment of that.

188
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:45,700
 And John's ministry really was to preach

189
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,320
 and to prepare God's people,

190
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:50,640
 prepare their heart to say that the Messiah will come.

191
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:53,820
 You just have to wait, you just have to be ready.

192
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:55,040
 And so in this passage,

193
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:59,120
 John's preaching represents God's calling,

194
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,840
 us out of the wilderness, out of our distractions,

195
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,360
 out of our busyness and hurrying and restlessness

196
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:08,040
 to receive the baptism of repentance

197
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:10,320
 for the forgiveness of sins

198
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:12,960
 and the baptism of the Holy Spirit.

199
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,680
 So this morning I want to spend time

200
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,760
 unpacking the significance of each baptism

201
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:20,720
 and why it is important for us as believers

202
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:24,240
 to receive or to know about these baptisms.

203
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:27,640
 In verse four, John the Baptist appears in the wilderness

204
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:30,520
 and begins preaching about the baptism of repentance

205
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,200
 for the forgiveness of sins.

206
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,440
 And so here are a few but brief thoughts

207
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,960
 on the significance of this water baptism.

208
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,600
 So let's start in the Old Testament.

209
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,600
 Wherever there is water imagery,

210
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:44,400
 it is typically alludes to the presence

211
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,920
 and the work of God's spirit.

212
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,480
 And of course in the New Testament,

213
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:51,240
 Jesus too uses water to describe the cleansing

214
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:53,840
 and renewing work of the Holy Spirit.

215
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:58,840
 And so to baptize is a verb that means to immerse.

216
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:01,240
 And so baptism as we understand it

217
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,680
 as from a church perspective

218
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,000
 and what we've been practicing

219
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,320
 all of these years and generations

220
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:10,160
 is baptism is the practice of immersing someone

221
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,600
 into the water.

222
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:14,440
 And by doing this, it represents a symbolic

223
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,760
 and a spiritual act of being born again,

224
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,800
 of being cleansed, being renewed,

225
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:22,480
 being resurrected with Christ in a new identity with him

226
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:26,360
 to have a new beginning in this life with God.

227
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,600
 And that's what we witness all the time.

228
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:32,720
 And so church, each of us will most likely

229
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:35,000
 just get baptized once in our lifetime

230
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,000
 as the physical, symbolic and spiritual declaration

231
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,240
 of our faith just as I've mentioned.

232
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:45,240
 And for majority of us, once is really enough.

233
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:49,560
 But within the heart and the idea behind baptism

234
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:52,480
 is the spiritual posturing of our own heart

235
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:58,160
 that has invaluable benefits in this life with Christ

236
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,240
 and the life to come.

237
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:05,240
 And so church, today I want us to ask God this,

238
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:08,720
 Lord, what does it mean to be baptized by you?

239
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:11,960
 What does it mean to be immersed by you

240
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:15,640
 and with you each day of our lives as your children?

241
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,560
 How does this look like?

242
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:20,240
 What must change in my heart for me to receive

243
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:23,440
 both these baptisms as a posturing of my heart,

244
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,880
 as my act of worship?

245
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:28,240
 Lord, I'm tired.

246
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,240
 This is for some of us.

247
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,960
 If we're tired, we're a bit cynical,

248
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,760
 we're a bit apathetic to this faith.

249
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,320
 We've been around for so long.

250
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:38,280
 How can I still receive the baptism

251
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,760
 that you have for me today?

252
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:44,000
 And so within the call to be baptized

253
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:48,040
 is a personal invitation to you to be transformed,

254
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,880
 to be renewed, to be immersed by God himself

255
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:54,980
 in his love as our way of life every single day.

256
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:57,080
 This is our spiritual journey.

257
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:59,560
 This is something we go on for the rest of our life.

258
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:03,080
 And that's our heart's cry when we want to be baptized.

259
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,340
 We're saying, Lord, I wanna be baptized by you.

260
00:12:05,340 --> 00:12:08,240
 I want you to lead me out of my wilderness.

261
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,000
 I wanna follow you wherever you are.

262
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,880
