00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,660
 and I do wanna just thank you for everyone

524
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:39,780
 that spearheaded that, you know who you are.

525
00:24:39,780 --> 00:24:43,740
 And, and just to be able to do what we as a church

526
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:46,220
 are called to do, which is to see others baptized,

527
00:24:46,220 --> 00:24:49,740
 to see people immersed in God's presence.

528
00:24:49,740 --> 00:24:52,620
 And I had time to actually read over a lot

529
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:55,060
 of the testimonies that were written

530
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:56,700
 by our brothers and sisters that day,

531
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,120
 and I want to just sum up.

532
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,100
 I don't have enough time to go through every one,

533
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:02,900
 but I wanna sum up the general, unique journey

534
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:04,460
 that each brother and sister took,

535
00:25:04,460 --> 00:25:07,260
 and that they moved from a place of desolation,

536
00:25:07,260 --> 00:25:09,740
 a place of isolation, the wilderness, the desert,

537
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:12,900
 to a place where, you know what, things are not perfect,

538
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:14,380
 they're not completely healed,

539
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:17,700
 but they got to a place where they could breathe again,

540
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:20,180
 where they could actually hear their thoughts again,

541
00:25:20,180 --> 00:25:22,060
 where they could be liberated,

542
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:24,220
 where they had a new perspective,

543
00:25:24,220 --> 00:25:28,500
 that they felt free to love and to speak

544
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:31,420
 and to know and that they're not alone.

545
00:25:31,420 --> 00:25:34,340
 And so this is the journey of baptism,

546
00:25:34,340 --> 00:25:36,180
 this is the posturing of our heart,

547
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:38,180
 and all these men and women before us,

548
00:25:38,180 --> 00:25:40,980
 on Sunday, November 8th, they said,

549
00:25:40,980 --> 00:25:44,420
 we found the way, and I declare and I confess,

550
00:25:44,420 --> 00:25:47,340
 this is the way I wanna continue to live from now on,

551
00:25:47,340 --> 00:25:50,140
 with our God leading us.

552
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:51,540
 And so I wanna share this quote

553
00:25:51,540 --> 00:25:54,180
 from a philosopher, theologian, Martin Buber,

554
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:57,620
 and I feel like he sums up this baptism,

555
00:25:57,620 --> 00:26:00,460
 our baptism journey, and also our reality,

556
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:02,860
 our shared reality as Christians.

557
00:26:02,860 --> 00:26:06,140
 He says, "God is no object of discourse,

558
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:08,180
 "knowledge, or even experience.

559
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:12,420
 "He cannot be spoken of, but He can be spoken to.

560
00:26:12,420 --> 00:26:16,100
 "He cannot be seen, but He can be listened to.

561
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:18,580
 "The only possible relationship with God

562
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:21,740
 "is to address Him and to be addressed by Him,

563
00:26:21,740 --> 00:26:23,220
 "here and now."

564
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:26,900
 Church, this describes the Christian life

565
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:28,980
 that all of us are on,

566
00:26:28,980 --> 00:26:31,740
 and the beauty of being addressed by God,

567
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:35,380
 and for us to address God and to listen to God,

568
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:36,820
 you know, it's not without struggles,

569
00:26:36,820 --> 00:26:40,220
 but it is what it is, and this is the beautiful gospel,

570
00:26:40,220 --> 00:26:42,540
 this is the life that all of us are called to.

571
00:26:42,540 --> 00:26:47,500
 And for me, each day, when I live out this baptism,

572
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,900
 each day is a new opportunity for me

573
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:52,380
 to call out to God in my wilderness

574
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:55,500
 of being distracted, of hurrying, of busyness,

575
00:26:55,500 --> 00:27:00,500
 of misplaced desires, of idolatry, of sin, and anger.

576
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:03,220
 You know, each day I cry out to God,

577
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:05,540
 and I say, "Lord, I don't wanna live like this anymore.

578
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:06,660
 "I can't live like this.

579
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:08,660
 "I can't bear to live like this,

580
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,180
 "so would you show me another way?

581
00:27:10,180 --> 00:27:12,300
 "I don't mind pain, I don't mind the suffer,

582
00:27:12,300 --> 00:27:13,940
 "but just show me another way.

583
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:16,100
 "Walk with me just through today.

584
00:27:16,100 --> 00:27:18,580
 "That's what I'm asking for, Lord."

585
00:27:18,580 --> 00:27:21,780
 And each day, I'm so forgetful, I just pray one thing.

586
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:25,140
 I say, "Lord, may I go through this day not to forget you,

587
00:27:25,140 --> 00:27:26,820
 "not to know that you sit with me."

588
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:30,500
 And I spend most of my energies just to remind myself

589
00:27:30,500 --> 00:27:33,500
 that He indeed is present with me.

590
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,780
 And in the last four to five months,

591
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:38,740
 I've actually been in the same spot with God.

592
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:41,340
 I've been surrendering more or less the same one thing.

593
00:27:41,340 --> 00:27:44,180
 I've been praying the same prayers every single day.

594
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:48,260
 My prayer is this, "Lord, baptize me,

595
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:51,520
 "immerse me in your presence, in your word,

596
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:54,760
 "and teach me not to be upset and angry

597
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:56,700
 "and lash out at my children."

598
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:59,620
 You know, and it's painful.

599
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:01,940
 It's humbling when your own children

600
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:03,660
 teach you how to parent.

601
00:28:03,660 --> 00:28:08,660
 But I think that's God speaking out of the wilderness to me.

602
00:28:08,660 --> 00:28:12,040
 And I think the important thing is to remain repentant,

603
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:15,100
 to be open, because God is God, right?

604
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:19,700
 He is the Lord of all creation, all over everything.

605
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:22,420
 And so I don't mind spending the rest of my life

606
00:28:22,420 --> 00:28:25,960
 just praying the same thing, learning what God has for me,

607
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:29,820
 if I am to grow to be more like Him.

608
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:30,860
 And so, church, I just wanna say,

609
00:28:30,860 --> 00:28:32,740
 don't be discouraged in where you are,

610
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:35,380
 because He is with you.

611
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:36,940
 And we're supposed to struggle,

612
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,940
 so don't be so hard on yourself.

613
00:28:38,940 --> 00:28:43,460
 If God can speak to me as I practice preaching,

614
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:44,780
 as I prepared for today,

615
00:28:44,780 --> 00:28:48,540
 He really just spoke to me at 11.20 last night,

616
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:52,420
 then I'm sure He can speak to you in any situation, church.

617
00:28:52,420 --> 00:28:55,160
 So practically, how does this look like

618
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,260
 for you and I to live out?

619
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:57,900
 I want to suggest three things

620
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:00,480
 that I've been personally adopting in my own life

621
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:04,080
 as a way to live out this idea and heart of baptism.

622
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:11,020
 And I just ask again, how do you and I posture ourselves

623
00:29:11,020 --> 00:29:13,840
 to be immersed in this way of life?

624
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:17,500
 First, I would say the key is to be always ready

625
00:29:17,500 --> 00:29:19,380
 to be repentant at any time.

626
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:22,680
 Guard your heart so that you're always ready

627
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,520
 and able to respond to God,

628
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:28,200
 even if it's just a very little thing

629
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,840
 that you can say or do.

630
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:33,760
 You know, God shows up in the most inconvenient times.

631
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,800
 He shows up in the most awkward times.

632
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:37,440
 He shows up in our conversations.

633
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,880
 He shows up with people we don't like,

634
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,480
 people who we don't even want to see,

635
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:45,160
 but yet God is there showing us in our disappointments,

636
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,920
 in our interruptions, in our pain and grief.

637
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:52,920
 He is there to show us Himself and to show us another way.

638
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:55,460
 And so that you will see, you'll be able to see

639
00:29:55,460 --> 00:30:00,460
 if you are willing to follow Him, new perspective.

640
00:30:00,460 --> 00:30:03,580
 And I think in this life, we will be distracted.

641
00:30:03,580 --> 00:30:04,700
 We will be busy.

642
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:07,700
 We will be tempted, but no matter what,

643
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:09,860
 always try to get back to this place

644
00:30:09,860 --> 00:30:12,500
 where your heart can say, "Lord, immerse me.

645
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:14,900
 "Lord, I know today's been really messed up,

646
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:18,400
 "but immerse me, that's all I need."

647
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:22,040
 Second suggestion is to immerse yourself in Scripture

648
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:25,300
 so that you can make room for the Holy Spirit in your life.

649
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:26,220
 Why do I say this?

650
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:28,700
 Because this is what Christians do.

651
00:30:28,700 --> 00:30:31,700
 This is what, this is the only way we know.

652
00:30:31,700 --> 00:30:32,940
 This is our way of life.

653
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:36,500
 Without letting Him address us with His words,

654
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,460
 we will not be able to live.

655
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:40,660
 You cannot discern God's voice

656
00:30:40,660 --> 00:30:42,540
 from the deception of the enemy,

657
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:45,900
 from the good and well-intentioned things of this world,

658
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:47,740
 from God's intention.

659
00:30:47,740 --> 00:30:51,380
 You know, and my prayer is really simple.

660
00:30:51,380 --> 00:30:54,140
 My prayer is, "Lord, when I wake up,

661
00:30:54,140 --> 00:30:56,820
 "I want you to be the first person that addresses me.

662
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:59,900
 "I want you to be the first person I talk to."

663
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:02,020
 And at night, I also just say,

664
00:31:02,020 --> 00:31:06,340
 "Lord, I pray that the person going to sleep right now

665
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:08,660
 "is different than the person who woke up

666
00:31:08,660 --> 00:31:11,480
 "because you encountered me, you spoke to me,

667
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:16,080
 "you changed my perspective, and I'm so thankful for that."

668
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:19,960
 Thirdly, lastly, I want to suggest

669
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:23,660
 to keep very short accounts in all our relationships.

670
00:31:23,660 --> 00:31:26,500
 You know, our ultimate test, I think, of our Christianity,

671
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:28,740
 whether it's genuine, whether it's sincere,

672
00:31:28,740 --> 00:31:31,220
 is simply in how we treat each other,

673
00:31:31,220 --> 00:31:33,340
 how we treat our parents, how we treat our children,

674
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:35,740
 how we treat our enemies, how we treat the stranger

675
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:36,860
 that we bump into the street

676
00:31:36,860 --> 00:31:38,140
 when we're in a really bad mood.

677
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:39,060
 What do we say to them?

678
00:31:39,060 --> 00:31:40,840
 How do we treat them?

679
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:46,180
 But the good news is God is in our relationship,

680
00:31:46,180 --> 00:31:50,880
 so whenever, in any relationship, God is there with us.

681
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,920
 And therefore, I think it's that important

682
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:56,720
 to prioritize managing our relationship

683
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:57,800
 and keeping short accounts,

684
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,840
 and that means to practice forgiveness.

685
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:01,360
 Because once again, I want to remind you,

686
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:05,380
 forgiveness removes all the barriers between us,

687
00:32:05,380 --> 00:32:07,680
 between God and us and between you and I.

688
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:13,480
 And, you know, my prayer has always been that

689
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:15,820
 if Christians can be known for anything,

690
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:18,640
 it's not for mistakes, it's not for hypocrisy,

691
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:21,120
 or, you know, what we didn't do, didn't say,

692
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:24,020
 but I pray that Christians would be known

693
00:32:24,020 --> 00:32:26,900
 for our forgiveness, that they would see Christ

694
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:28,840
 because in how we choose to forgive,

695
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:30,620
 because God has forgiven us.

696
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:35,300
 So, church, if I can sum up the last 25 minutes,

697
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:38,160
 I would say today is really about the work of God

698
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:41,120
 and the Holy Spirit and what he desires to do in our life.

699
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:46,720
 In this Advent season, and in every season of our life,

700
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,680
 this baptism of water and the Holy Spirit

701
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:54,220
 represents his invitation to come on a lifelong journey,

702
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:58,060
 a pilgrimage, a spiritual journey with the triune God

703
00:32:58,060 --> 00:33:01,480
 who leads us to be truly free,

704
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:05,840
 to be truly ourselves in his presence every single day.

705
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:09,600
 So the simple question I ask you is, will you join him?

706
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:11,480
 Will you let him satisfy you?

707
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:14,360
 Will you let him address you and transform you?

708
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:19,360
 Will you allow him to immerse himself and his love upon you?

709
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:24,080
 Closing, in closing, church, I wanna say this.

710
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:25,860
 Do you remember the Great Commission?

711
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:27,260
 What does Jesus say there?

712
00:33:27,260 --> 00:33:29,520
 And I wanna remind you what the Great Commission says.

713
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:33,380
 He says, "So you must go and make all the nations

714
00:33:33,380 --> 00:33:36,960
 "into disciples, baptizing them in the name of the Father

715
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,860
 "and the Son and the Holy Spirit.

716
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:41,400
 "Teach them to observe everything I've commanded you,

717
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:44,180
 "and look, I am with you every single day

718
00:33:44,180 --> 00:33:46,300
 "to the very end of age."

719
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:49,640
 Note that Jesus calls us to baptize the nations,

720
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:53,040
 baptize whoever we seize in the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit

721
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:56,880
 as in we are called as Christians to immerse others

722
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:58,840
 in everything we know about God,

723
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,480
 everything Jesus has given us,

724
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,880
 everything that the Holy Spirit is showing us,

725
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:06,960
 we are called to immerse others with this,

726
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:09,280
 and this is a command.

727
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:12,580
 And so what I really wanna remind us before we go

728
00:34:12,580 --> 00:34:15,880
 is that our faith must go beyond ourselves.

729
00:34:15,880 --> 00:34:19,800
 We immerse ourselves, we transform, we are changed,

730
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:22,360
 not for our own sake, but the sake of our neighbor,

731
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,840
 for the sake of our enemy.

732
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:28,920
 And so having after received God's presence,

733
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:32,240
 we too then must go out and share the presence of God,

734
00:34:32,240 --> 00:34:36,280
 the love of God, whatever God has given us with others,

735
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:39,200
 and so that others may know that there is a journey

736
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:42,120
 that God yearns to bring each of us on.

737
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:46,500
 And so this is what the Christian life is all about,

738
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:49,160
 and I pray that the Spirit will lead you

739
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:53,320
 from wherever you are today to walk with Him.

740
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,420
 Church, can we pray?

741
00:34:54,420 --> 00:35:03,740
 Father, you say if we confess our sins, you are faithful,

742
00:35:03,740 --> 00:35:07,140
 you are just, and you will forgive us and will cleanse us.

743
00:35:07,140 --> 00:35:11,140
 You will wash us thoroughly from all that cages us

744
00:35:11,140 --> 00:35:12,860
 and causes us to be stuck.

745
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:17,740
 You will free us, you will be able to make us whole again.

746
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:22,740
 So God, today, right now, we ask that you create in us

747
00:35:22,740 --> 00:35:25,000
 a renewed spirit.

748
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:28,580
 Father, would your Spirit come and dwell in us.

749
00:35:28,580 --> 00:35:31,980
 Immerse us, Lord God.

750
00:35:31,980 --> 00:35:35,760
 Father, let us be with you.

751
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:38,980
 Wherever you are, we confess we want to follow

752
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:40,240
 and be with you.

753
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:46,240
 And Lord, as children, we ask, Lord God,

754
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:50,340
 that the one thing is that you would make yourself real

755
00:35:50,340 --> 00:35:53,260
 to us today, right now.

756
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:56,400
 Whatever it takes, Lord God, to get our attention,

757
00:35:56,400 --> 00:36:00,960
 Father, I pray that at the end of today, before we sleep,

758
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:05,600
 our hearts would say, Lord, you are the living God.

759
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:07,080
 You, I will follow.

760
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:09,320
 You, I will learn more about.

761
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:12,800
 And one day, I might follow you,

762
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:15,920
 or maybe we'll say, Lord, thank you for being with me.

763
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,260
 Thank you for immersing me.

764
00:36:17,260 --> 00:36:20,360
 Thank you for reminding me that I'm not alone,

765
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,920
 that I don't struggle alone.

766
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:24,820
 I don't go through anything alone because you are with me.

767
00:36:24,820 --> 00:36:28,260
 And so Jesus, this is our prayer.

768
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:33,260
 In your beautiful name, would you continue to speak to us

769
00:36:33,260 --> 00:36:37,500
 every single moment you give to us in this precious life.

770
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:41,160
 And Lord, teach us to steward and treasure

771
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:44,680
 the greatest treasure we will ever, ever receive,

772
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:45,620
 and that is you.

773
00:36:45,620 --> 00:36:48,580
 In your name we pray, amen.

774
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:51,160
 (gentle music)

